Riposte						KEY:Scout ACF ~ Riposte														CATEGORY:ACF			TYPE:ScoutSkirmish.ACF																																						PREMULT:2,[PRECLASS:1,Scout=1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Skirmish]																																																														DESC:This replaces the skirmish feature to let you do the extra damage and benefit from the AC boost against any foe that attacked you the previous round.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Scout ACF ~ RiposteSA																																																																																																																																																																																																																										COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:WebEn 6
Riposte						KEY:Scout ACF ~ RiposteSA													CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary								VISIBLE:YES																																																																																																				DESC:[Skirmish +%1d6]|(SkirmishLVL+3)/4	DESC:[AC Bonus +%1]|(SkirmishLVL+1)/4	DESC:A riposting scout relies on taking advantage of the openings provided by their foes to deal extra damage and improve her defense. She deals an extra %1d6 points of damage on all attacks she makes against an opponent that attacked her (successfully or not) during the previous round. The extra damage applies only against living creatures that have a discernible anatomy. Undead, constructs, oozes, plants, incorporeal creatures, and creatures immune to extra damage from critical hits are not vulnerable to this additional damage. The scout must be able to see the target well enough to pick out a vital spot and must be able to reach such a spot. She can apply this extra damage to ranged attacks, but only if the target is within 30 feet. At 3rd level and beyond, a scout gains a +%2 competence bonus to Armor Class against any creature to which she has dealt riposte damage. This lasts until the start of her next turn. A scout loses this ability when wearing medium or heavy armor or when carrying a medium or heavy load.|(SkirmishLVL+3)/4|(SkirmishLVL+1)/4																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:WebEn 6
