Weapon and Armor Proficiency			KEY:Crimson Scourge ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency		OUTPUTNAME:Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialQuality										VISIBLE:YES																																																																																																				DESC:You are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, light and medium armor, and shields (but not tower shields). In additional you can select one of the following as a free weapon proficiency: bolas, net, or whip																																																																																																																																																																																																																														AUTO:ARMORPROF|ARMORTYPE=Light|ARMORTYPE=Medium	AUTO:SHIELDPROF|SHIELDTYPE=Buckler|SHIELDTYPE=Light|SHIELDTYPE=Heavy	AUTO:WEAPONPROF|TYPE=Simple|TYPE=Martial																																				BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Crimson Scourge Weapon Profs|1																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:93
Kid Gloves						KEY:Crimson Scourge ~ Kid Gloves					OUTPUTNAME:Kid Gloves				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary								VISIBLE:YES																																																																																																				DESC:Crimson scourges excel at manipulating the wounds that they inflict, causing more or less harm as the situation demands. If you choose, you can deal nonlethal damage with weapons that normally deal lethal damage, or lethal damage with weapons that normally deal nonlethal damage-both without taking the usual -4 penalty on the attack roll.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:93
Special Dispensation				KEY:Crimson Scourge ~ Special Dispensation			OUTPUTNAME:Special Dispensation		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialQuality										VISIBLE:YES																																																																																																				DESC:Crimson scourges do not operate in secrecy unless they have to, so their patrons provide them the freedom to perform their duties. While operating in any area where bounty hunting is acceptable, a slavers guild has any presence, or you enjoy the patronage of an influential figure, you gain the benefit of the Special Dispensation feat, even if you do not meet the prerequisites.																																																																																																																																																																																																																													VFEAT:Special Dispensation																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:93
Swift Tracker					KEY:Crimson Scourge ~ Swift Tracker					OUTPUTNAME:Swift Tracker			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary								VISIBLE:YES																																																																																																				DESC:Starting at 2nd level, you can make a Gather Information check when using Urban Tracking every half-hour without taking the usual -5 penalty.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:93
Painful Strike					KEY:Crimson Scourge ~ Painful Strike				OUTPUTNAME:Painful Strike			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary								VISIBLE:YES																																												DEFINE:PainfulStrike|0																																																					DESC:You have gained the ability to deal an extra %1d6 points of nonlethal damage against an unarmed opponent. This ability does not function if the opponent has a weapon of any sort in either hand, or if your attack deals lethal damage. Unarmed foes with the Improved Unarmed Strike feat are still considered unarmed. This ability never applies to ranged attacks, regardless of proximity. If you score a critical hit, this bonus damage is not multiplied. Creatures immune to nonlethal damage as well as constructs, oozes, plants, and incorporeal creatures are not affected by this ability.|PainfulStrike																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:93
Immovable Heart					KEY:Crimson Scourge ~ Immovable Heart				OUTPUTNAME:Immovable Heart			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassAbility.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary								VISIBLE:YES																																																																																																				DESC:Your grim profession hardens your emotions. You gain a +2 competence bonus to resist enchantment spells and fear effects.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:93		ASPECT:SaveBonus|+2 vs. Enchantment spells and fear effects
